ObAgent: uncertain

Analysis: multiple servers show elevated TCP FIN/CLOSE-WAIT counts and many open DB/Redis connection metrics plus high InnoDB row lock time — this could be network-induced connection buildup, or backend/resource saturation (DB or app) causing connections to hang. To disambiguate, check:
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for OSLinux CPU (system.cpu.*) on Mysql01/Tomcat* (detect high CPU);
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for OSLinux_NETWORK_NETWORK_TCP_RETRANS and any RTT/latency metrics on MG*/IG* (detect packet loss/latency);
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for Mysql: Threads_connected, Innodb_row_lock_time, Open_tables, Queries_per_sec (detect DB contention);
- if needed, collect_trace on Tomcat→MySQL call paths to see where calls are blocking.
JudgeAgent: No - Not found — the agents only hypothesized a high-CPU class but did not pin a single component, one anomaly type instance (specific KPI/log/trace) and one exact occurrence minute. Evidence shows multiple candidate hosts with CPU/trace anomalies at different minutes (e.g., Tomcat03 OSLinux-CPU_CPU-0 SingleCpuUtil = 92.55 at 2021-03-07 16:19:00; MG02 OSLinux-CPU_CPU-2 = 88.07 at 2021-03-07 16:29:00; IG01 trace.self.duration_p95 = 61 at 2021-03-07 16:00:00), so the root cause location and single occurrence datetime were not uniquely identified.

